                "name": "Micayla Lenski",
                "href": "/profile/Micayla-Lenski"
            },
            "answer_text": "I would say you are indeed a Biromantic Homosexual, which is perfectly valid! Your description of yourself is the exact definition of a Biromantic Homosexual. You are open to romantic relationships with both men and women (Biromantic), but you are only open to sexual relationships with men (Homosexual). This sexuality is somewhat of a minority, but that is perfectly okay! (I myself am also an LGBT+ minority, being Panromantic Demisexual) However, it is also perfectly okay to identify as Bisexual, since this term can be sort of an umbrella term for all things Bi- and Homo-. I do this in my situation as well. If I meet someone, and the topic of my sexuality comes up, I simply say I am Pansexual. If I then feel that I can explain myself into further detail, I would go deeper into my label, explaining I am actually Panromantic Demisexual. (Romantically attracted to anyone, regardless of gender, but only sexually attracted to those that I have a strong bond with) I would advise that you try this as well, as it has worked fairly well for me! ",
