            "author_info": {
                "name": "Grace Duncan",
                "href": "/profile/Grace-Duncan-4"
            },
            "answer_text": "Hey, I was in the same situation but with opposite genders. I'm a female mostly interested in women but I could see myself with a man. I choose to label myself as bisexual (or pansexual if I think they'll know the term) because it doesn't put me in the 100% gay box. I think there's a big misconception that bi/pansexuality is sexual attraction to everyone equally when it's really not. Even with heterosexual people we know they're not attracted to everyone of the opposite gender. Just like that, it's ok to be bisexual and prefer one gender over the other. At the end of the day though it is your decision. The reason I choose the term bisexual is because I want people to know that I'm open to all genders, whether I'm attracted to them back or not is just chance just as with any other sexuality and relationship. Good luck :) ",
